To uninstall Java on a Windows system, follow these steps:

Open Control Panel:
Press Win + S to open the search bar, type "Control Panel," and click on it.
Navigate to Programs:

Select Programs > Programs and Features.
Locate Java:
Scroll through the list to find Java or Java SE Development Kit (you might see multiple versions if more than one is installed).

Uninstall Java:
Right-click on the Java entry you want to remove, then select Uninstall. Follow the on-screen prompts to complete the uninstallation.
Remove Environment Variables (Optional):

If you want to remove any remaining paths, press Win + S, type "Environment Variables," and open it.
In System Properties, select Environment Variables and look for any Java-related paths (usually under Path) to delete them.
